Aim

To simulate TCP/IP stack using a network protocol analyzer and analyze the network traffic.

Software Used
Wireshark

Theory
TCP/IP Stack

TCP/IP is a set of communication protocols used for networking.

Layers of TCP/IP Model
Application Layer – HTTP, FTP, DNS
Transport Layer – TCP, UDP
Internet Layer – IP
Network Access Layer – Ethernet
Protocol Analyzer

A network protocol analyzer captures and analyzes packets flowing through a network.

Helps in troubleshooting
Monitors traffic
Shows real-time packet details
Working
Captures packets from network interface
Displays protocol details like IP, TCP, HTTP
Allows filtering and analysis

Procedure

Step 1: Install and Open Tool
Open Wireshark
Step 2: Select Interface
Choose active network interface (Wi-Fi/Ethernet)
Step 3: Start Capturing
Click Start Capture
Step 4: Generate Traffic
Open browser and visit any website
Example: www.google.com
Step 5: Stop Capture
Click Stop after few seconds
Step 6: Analyze Packets
Observe:
Source & Destination IP
Protocols (TCP, HTTP, DNS)
Packet length
Apply filters:
tcp → shows TCP packets
http → shows HTTP traffic
dns → shows DNS queries
Step 7: Study TCP/IP Layers
Expand packet details
Identify:
Ethernet → Network Access Layer
IP → Internet Layer
TCP → Transport Layer
HTTP/DNS → Application Layer

Result

TCP/IP stack was successfully simulated using Wireshark. Network traffic was captured and analyzed, and different protocol layers were observed.
